title: Print, Title page of Neuw Grotteschenbuch (suite 3), 1610
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of the Estate of David Wolfe Bishop
description:
An elaborate frame, in the form of a sheet, stretched from the boughs of a tree with various ornamental forms as fruit, contains the title. Below, a broad landscape, including a large body of water.

Translation of title: Der Ratseckisch Radesco tree of which one has never seen the like because it bears weird kinds of fruit which one can see here with one's own eyes through Christoph Jamnitzer citizen and goldsmith in Nuremberg, polished by [Jor Z]ola.

tombstone.epitaph:
Print, Title page of Neuw Grotteschenbuch (suite 3), 1610. Black ink on white paper. 
Museum purchase through gift of the Estate of David Wolfe Bishop. 1957-162-21
